<p>Use cursor utility classes to control the mouse pointer appearance on
hover. These classes map directly to standard CSS <code>cursor</code>
values, making it easy to indicate interactivity or context.</p>
<h3 id="doc-syntax">Syntax</h3>
<pre><code>.cursor-[value]</code></pre>
<p>Where <code>[value]</code> is a supported cursor type.</p>
